# CODEOWNERS — review-required ownership map.
#
# Every match in this file requires the listed owner(s) to approve a PR
# before it can merge into main. Branch protection on `main` enforces
# this via the "Require review from Code Owners" setting (see
# docs/releasing.md for the full UI configuration).
#
# The file is matched bottom-to-top: the LAST matching entry wins. Order
# the rules from broad (top) to narrow (bottom) so specific paths
# override the catch-all. Path-specific entries below intentionally
# duplicate the catch-all owner; their purpose is to document intent so
# a future editor knows the path is security-sensitive when the team
# membership is reviewed.
#
# OWNER NOTE: until a dedicated `@axonops/audit-maintainers` GitHub
# team is created, individual maintainer handles are listed below. The
# maintainer onboarding step in docs/releasing.md will switch to the
# team handle once it exists.

# Catch-all default — a maintainer must review every change.
*                                       @millerjp

# CI/CD and release infrastructure.
.github/                                @millerjp
.github/workflows/                      @millerjp
.github/CODEOWNERS                      @millerjp
.github/dependabot.yml                  @millerjp

# GoReleaser config — affects every published artefact and Cosign sig.
.goreleaser.yml                         @millerjp

# Module manifests — affect the public API surface and dependency graph.
# `**/go.mod` matches the root file too (zero or more path segments).
**/go.mod                               @millerjp
**/go.sum                               @millerjp

# Build orchestration. The Makefile, the release toolchain scripts,
# and pinned tool versions all run under the release-bot's elevated
# token at release time — a malicious edit could exfiltrate it.
Makefile                                @millerjp
scripts/release/                        @millerjp
scripts/tool-versions.txt               @millerjp
tests/release/                          @millerjp

# Security policy and threat model.
SECURITY.md                             @millerjp
docs/threat-model.md                    @millerjp

# Release process and deployment documentation — change controls match
# the corresponding GitHub UI settings.
docs/releasing.md                       @millerjp
docs/deployment.md                      @millerjp

# Cryptographic primitives — extra scrutiny.
hmac.go                                 @millerjp
ssrf.go                                 @millerjp
ssrf_*.go                               @millerjp
tls_policy.go                           @millerjp
secrets/                                @millerjp

# Public test helpers — used by every consumer's test suite.
audittest/                              @millerjp

# Code generator template — output ships into every consumer.
cmd/audit-gen/template.go               @millerjp
